fields.name: Push-Up
fields.description: A classic bodyweight exercise for upper body strength.
fields.instructions: Start in a plank position, lower your body until your chest nearly touches the floor, then push up.

fields.name: Squat
fields.description: A fundamental lower-body exercise.
fields.instructions: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, lower your hips as if sitting in a chair, then stand back up.

fields.name: deadlift
fields.description: A strength exercise to build posterior chain muscles.
fields.instructions: Stand behind a barbell, hinge at your hips, lift the barbell while keeping your back straight, then lower.

fields.name: Bench Press
fields.description: A staple exercise for upper body strength.
fields.instructions: Lie on a bench, lower the barbell to your chest, then press it back up.

fields.name: Pull-Up
fields.description: A bodyweight exercise for back and arm strength.
fields.instructions: Grip the pull-up bar, pull yourself up until your chin is above the bar, then lower back down.

fields.name: Plank
fields.description: A core stabilization exercise.
fields.instructions: Hold a push-up position, keeping your body in a straight line.

fields.name: Lunge
fields.description: An excellent exercise for lower-body strength and balance.
fields.instructions: Step forward with one leg, lower your body until both knees are bent, then return to standing.

fields.name: Bicep Curl
fields.description: A basic exercise for arm strength.
fields.instructions: Hold dumbbells at your sides, curl them up to shoulder height, then lower back down.

fields.name: Tricep Dip
fields.description: A bodyweight exercise for the triceps.
fields.instructions: Use parallel bars or a sturdy chair, lower your body by bending your elbows, then push back up.

fields.name: Leg Press
fields.description: A machine-based lower-body exercise.
fields.instructions: Sit on the machine, push the platform with your legs, then return to the starting position.

fields.name: Calf Raise
fields.description: An exercise for the calves.
fields.instructions: Stand on a raised surface, lift your heels as high as possible, then lower back down.

fields.name: Shoulder Press
fields.description: A strength exercise for the shoulders.
fields.instructions: Press dumbbells or a barbell overhead, then return to shoulder height.

fields.name: Crunch
fields.description: A popular abdominal exercise.
fields.instructions: Lie on your back, curl your torso towards your knees, then return to the starting position.

fields.name: Russian Twist
fields.description: A core exercise focusing on obliques.
fields.instructions: Sit on the floor, lean back slightly, twist your torso from side to side.

fields.name: Rowing
fields.description: A full-body cardiovascular and strength exercise.
fields.instructions: Use a rowing machine, pulling the handle towards your chest, then extend back.

fields.name: Burpee
fields.description: A full-body explosive movement.
fields.instructions: Start standing, drop into a squat, kick back into a plank, return to squat, then jump up.

fields.name: Kettlebell Swing
fields.description: A dynamic exercise for power and conditioning.
fields.instructions: Swing a kettlebell between your legs, then up to shoulder height using your hips.

fields.name: Dumbbell Fly
fields.description: An isolation exercise for the chest.
fields.instructions: Lie on a bench, hold dumbbells above your chest, lower them out to your sides, then bring them back up.

fields.name: Mountain Climber
fields.description: A cardio and core exercise.
fields.instructions: Start in a plank, alternate driving your knees towards your chest quickly.

fields.name: Side Plank
fields.description: A core stability exercise.
fields.instructions: Lie on one side, prop yourself up on one elbow, hold your body straight.
